      <content>
        <section toc="false">
          <marginalnote>Interpretation</marginalnote>
          <sectionnumber>1</sectionnumber>
          <sectiontext>In this regulation, <term>Act</term> means the <actname>Police Act</actname>.</sectiontext>
        </section>
        <section>
          <marginalnote>Record of complaint</marginalnote>
          <sectionnumber>2</sectionnumber>
          <sectiontext>A record of complaint under section 52 (4) of the Act must be in Form 1.</sectiontext>
        </section>
        <section>
          <marginalnote>Notice of discipline proceeding</marginalnote>
          <sectionnumber>3</sectionnumber>
          <sectiontext>A notice of a discipline proceeding under section 58.1 (1) (c) of the Act must be in Form 2.</sectiontext>
        </section>
        <section>
          <marginalnote>Findings of discipline authority</marginalnote>
          <sectionnumber>4</sectionnumber>
          <subsection>
            <subsectionnumber>1</subsectionnumber>
            <subsectiontext>The findings of a discipline authority at a discipline proceeding under section 59 (5) (b) of the Act must be recorded in Form 3.</subsectiontext>
          </subsection>
          <subsection>
            <subsectionnumber>2</subsectionnumber>
            <subsectiontext>Within 10 business days after hearing submissions from the respondent, or his or her agent or counsel, at the conclusion of a discipline proceeding under section 59 (5) of the Act, the discipline authority must serve a copy of the discipline authority's findings, recorded in Form 3, on the respondent.</subsectiontext>
          </subsection>
        </section>
        <section>
          <marginalnote>Disposition record</marginalnote>
          <sectionnumber>5</sectionnumber>
          <sectiontext>A disposition record under section 59 (6) of the Act must be in Form 4.</sectiontext>
        </section>
